cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.DC

This paper deals with the analysis of Internet-wide activity at individual IP address-level granularity, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the identification and attribution of activity patterns to network restructurings, user behaviors, and address assignment practices, which could be classified under the sub-category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper also presents novel perspectives on worldwide IPv4 address activity, which could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the utilization of IP addresses in different areas, which could be classified under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
